snippet.textDisplay: Pashto is the second most spoken language in Pakistan. Out of the 5 capital cities, Peshawar and Quetta are predominantly pashtun cities. The very recently unearthed oldest (1800 years) sleeping statue of Buddha in KPK reflects the rich cultural heritage that the Pashtuns inherit. Including one Pashto song this season speaks volumes of the importance of this race and region in the national attire of this country. God bless the 'federation' of Pakistan.
